ny stories about the events that led to the fall of the empire. Most of them contradict each other. Very little of worth is recalled about this event save that a vast disaster occurred which destroyed the world. What caused it is one of the mysteries that may never be solved. Some say it was a natural disaster – a black hole strayed too close or a sun went nova near to the earth.  Others claim that it was a technical fault which caused the accident.  Yet more claim a darker conspiracy and say that it was terrorists, enemies of the empire, who sabotaged the world for their own evil ends.  <br>
<br>
Whatever or whoever caused the Sundering, the consequences cannot be denied. No other event in all history is so central, so global as is the Sundering. In a single day, it reshaped the world, reforged the heavens and rewrote the histories and calendars of man. It swept o'er the world leaving no thing untouched. It was and is the great equalizer. It divides the present from the past. It cleaves what is from what could have been. It is the force of ages. It is the crucible of our world.<br>
